---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Compatibility ‚Äî Tebian">
	<main>
		<article class="doc">
			<h1>Compatibility</h1>
			<p class="lead">The OS that runs other OSs.</p>

			<section class="meta-layer">
				<p>Tebian isn't just a Linux distribution; it's a bridge. We recognize that sometimes you need tools from other ecosystems. Instead of switching machines, we bring those ecosystems to you.</p>
				
				<div class="compat-grid">
					<div class="compat-card">
						<span class="compat-icon">üçé</span>
						<h3>t-mac</h3>
						<p>One-click macOS VM setup (OSX-KVM). Access Xcode, iOS development, and the App Store with full USB passthrough and iCloud support.</p>
						<code class="compat-cmd">fuzzel ‚Üí Virtualization ‚Üí Setup macOS</code>
					</div>
					<div class="compat-card">
						<span class="compat-icon">ü™ü</span>
						<h3>t-win</h3>
						<p>Guided dual-boot partitioning for Anti-Cheat games and proprietary software that won't run in a VM. Safe, automated, and GRUB-integrated.</p>
						<code class="compat-cmd">fuzzel ‚Üí Virtualization ‚Üí Setup Windows</code>
					</div>
					<div class="compat-card">
						<span class="compat-icon">ü§ñ</span>
						<h3>t-droid</h3>
						<p>Run Android apps natively on your desktop via Waydroid. No emulation, just containerized performance for your mobile-only tools.</p>
						<code class="compat-cmd">fuzzel ‚Üí Software ‚Üí Android Mode</code>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="philosophy">
				<h2>No Compromise</h2>
				<p>Most Linux users feel forced to keep a second "sacrificial" machine for work or gaming. Tebian eliminates this. We prioritize virtualization and dual-boot logic so you can have 100% compatibility without ever sacrificing your privacy or stability.</p>
			</section>
		</article>

		<div class="nav">
			<a href="/">‚Üê Back</a>
			<span class="nav-divider">|</span>
			<a href="/source">Source</a>
			<a href="/architecture">Architecture</a>
			<a href="/rig">Rig</a>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		width: 100%;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.doc {
		max-width: 850px;
		width: 100%;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		color: var(--accent-color);
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.lead {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		color: #9399b2;
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		font-style: italic;
	}

	section {
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		color: #cdd6f4;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-color);
		padding-left: 1rem;
	}

	.compat-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	.compat-card {
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
		padding: 2rem;
		border-radius: 12px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
		transition: all 0.3s ease;
	}

	.compat-card:hover {
		border-color: var(--accent-color);
		background: rgba(137, 180, 250, 0.03);
		transform: translateY(-5px);
	}

	.compat-icon {
		font-size: 2rem;
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.compat-card h3 {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
		color: #bac2de;
	}

	.compat-card p {
		color: #9399b2;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.compat-cmd {
		display: block;
		background: #000;
		padding: 0.75rem;
		border-radius: 6px;
		color: #a6e3a1;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		font-family: monospace;
		border: 1px solid rgba(166, 227, 161, 0.1);
	}

	.nav {
		margin-top: 2rem;
		display: flex;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.nav a {
		color: #6c7086;
		text-decoration: none;
		font-size: 1rem;
		transition: color 0.2s;
	}

	.nav a:hover {
		color: var(--accent-color);
	}

	.nav-divider {
		color: #313244;
	}
</style>